-case subtype.attitude.ordinal
-when "fourth"
  Don’t #{subtype.produce} in the evening, even if you feel alert and productive. Try not to #{subtype.produce} at midday either. In fact, avoid or postpone #{subtype.produce.ing} whenever you can. When you have to #{subtype.change_nouns}, use more #{subtype.stamina} not more #{subtype.strength}.
-when "third"
  Do #{subtype.consume} every evening, even if you feel alert and productive. If you have time, #{subtype.consume} at midday also. When you #{subtype.consume}, try to #{subtype.get_nice_energy} rather than #{subtype.strengtheners}. Don’t #{subtype.produce} if you don’t have any #{subtype.nouns} you want to #{subtype.change}.
-when "second"
  Do #{subtype.produce} every morning, even if you feel calm and receptive. If you have time, #{subtype.produce} in the afternoon also. When you #{subtype.produce}, try to use more #{subtype.strength} than #{subtype.stamina}. Don’t bother #{subtype.consume.ing} just because the #{subtype.energizers} are #{subtype.nice}; you need #{subtype.strengtheners} to develop your #{subtype.strength}.
-when "first"
  Don’t #{subtype.consume} in the morning, even if you feel calm and receptive. Try not to #{subtype.consume} in the afternoon either. In fact, avoid or postpone #{subtype.consume.ing} whenever you can. When you do #{subtype.consume}, #{subtype.get_strength} instead of #{subtype.energizers}.
